    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.711/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-20T22:00:00+00:00"
                            >August 20, 1936—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 21—3:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>X–77. Decree of August 15 published in the <hi rend="italic">Gaceta de
                        Madrid</hi> of August 18th establishes censorship all incoming and outgoing
                    mail. At meeting of the Diplomatic Corps today Swiss, German and several other
                    representatives reported that mail addressed to them bearing official seal had
                    been opened. All have brought these incidents to attention of the Foreign
                    Office. Anticipating such possibility I have <pb facs="0777" n="678"
                        xml:id="pg_678"/> requested Ambassador Bowers at Hendaye,<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d665fn97">The Chancery was moved to Hotel Eskualduna, Hendaye, on
                        August 13 (124. 521/142).</note> Embassy, Paris and Consulates Barcelona and
                    Valencia not to forward confidential material to this Embassy by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
